    skos:definition "The sum of all dead organic components at various stages of decomposition in a soil, which are made from basic elements including carbon, nitrogen, oxygen, hydrogen and an array of attached cations and ions." ;
    skos:definition "Some definitions include undecayed plant and animal residues as well as microbial biomass." ;
    agrontology:isMadeFrom she:Carbon, she:Nitrogen, she:Oxygen, she:Hydrogen, she:PlantResidues, she:AnimalResidues, she:MicrobialBiomass .

